issue.title: error when creating model

issue.body:
hi,

Trying to train this. when running :
```
from efficientnet import EfficientNetB0
import keras
from keras.layers import Activation, Dense, Multiply, Input, Flatten, Dropout, Conv2D, BatchNormalization


inp_mask = Input(shape=(512,512,3))
bn_inp = inp_mask
pretrain_model_mask = EfficientNetB0(
input_shape=(512, 512, 3),  #SWITCH
include_top=False,
weights='imagenet',
#        dropout=0.5,
#        pooling='max'
)(bn_inp)

```

I get the following


body:
@qubvel A simple fix would be to extend the `Initializer` class in `keras.initializers` and wrap the `conv_initiatializer` and `dense_initializer` code inside `__call__`, and use objects of that class as the initializer for conv and dense respectively.

You would also need to register the two classes as custom objects, which would allow load_model to work without issue.

Hi @titu1994
Thanks for advice, I will do it that way!
